## Sections Explained

### 1. Overview
Provides context about the feature - what it does, why it's needed, who's involved, and what's in/out of scope.

### 2. Requirements Summary
Maps back to Phase 1 requirements, showing functional and non-functional requirements in table format for easy tracking.

### 3. Architecture
Describes the high-level system design, component structure, and data flow. Include diagrams where helpful.

### 4. Data Models
Defines all data structures used in the system - frontend types, backend models, and database schemas.

### 5. API Specification
Documents all API endpoints with full request/response examples. Critical for frontend-backend contract.

### 6. State Management
Describes how application state is managed - global state, server state, local state patterns.

### 7. Security Considerations
Addresses authentication, authorization, input validation, data protection, and rate limiting.

### 8. Performance Considerations
Sets performance targets and describes optimization strategies for frontend, backend, and network.

### 9. Error Handling
Defines how errors are handled at each layer and what messages users see.

### 10. Testing Strategy
Maps to Phase 4 test planning - defines test types, coverage targets, and critical test scenarios.

### 11. Deployment Strategy
Describes environments, feature flags, rollout strategy, and monitoring approach.

### 12. Rollback Plan
Defines when and how to rollback if issues occur in production.

### 13. Documentation
Lists all documentation that will be created - code docs, user guides, developer guides.

### 14. Success Metrics
Defines technical and business metrics to measure success.

### 15. Risks & Mitigations
Identifies potential risks and mitigation strategies.

### 16. Dependencies
Lists all dependencies - libraries, external services, internal systems.

### 17. Timeline & Milestones
Estimates time for each phase of work.

### 18. Approval & Sign-off
Tracks stakeholder approval.

